Step 1 — Clone repo on Friend's Laptop
Run this in the terminal on the friend's laptop:
powershellcd C:\
git clone https://github.com/shivangsudhakar999/FinTrack-Expense-Splitting.git
cd FinTrack-Expense-Splitting
code .
This opens the repo in VS Code on the friend's laptop.

Step 2 — Set up the folder structure
Run this in the friend's laptop terminal inside the project:
powershellmkdir -p .claude/rules, src/transactions, tests
New-Item CLAUDE.md -ItemType File
New-Item README.md -ItemType File
New-Item requirements.txt -ItemType File

Step 3 — Login to Claude Code
powershellclaude
It will open a browser — log in with your Anthropic account, then come back to terminal.

